content:
The Agents tab in Omni Supervisor provides a simple way to keep up with your agents' presence statuses, channels, assigned queues, and open capacity. You can see how long your agents have been logged in and when they last accepted new work.

Available in: Salesforce Classic (not available in all orgs), Lightning Experience
Omni Supervisor is available in: Essentials, Professional, Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer Editions

There are two views in the Agents tab: All Agents and Agents by Queue.

All Agents Subtab:
- Allows you to see the big picture of your agents' availability, capabilities, capacity, and workload.
- Displays agents logged into Omni-Channel with status, channels, queues, workload, and capacity.
- Enables changing an agent's status using the Action column (offline agents not tracked).
- Includes Agent Detail and Agent Timeline views for more information.

Agents by Queue Subtab:
- Provides information about how well your queues are covered.
- Displays every queue with at least one online or away agent, showing assigned agents and their status.

Fields include:
- Presence status
- Channels
- Assigned queues
- Open capacity

When a voice call is active, it consumes 100% of an agent's capacity. After conversation work (ACW) frees up agent capacity after the ACW period ends or the agent closes the tab, whichever happens first.
title: Omni-Channel Agent Management with Service Cloud
